416,"sic":417},"δ","γ",{"supplied":419},{"_":420,"reason":384,"cert":73},"ἡμῖν",{"_":422,"supplied":423},"ν",{"_":424,"reason":384},"τὴ","ἒνβασιν",{"type":427,"resp":353,"listApp":428},"apparatus",{"app":429},[430,432,434,436,438,442],{"note":431},"Text based on photographs",{"loc":374,"note":433},"Ferrua, Korhonen: ((Chi-rho)); Kaibel: Μ(ᾶρκος)",{"loc":398,"note":435},"Franz: Ῥεστ[ιτ]οῦτος",{"loc":378,"note":437},"Franz: ἠγοράσαμεν; Kaibel, Wessel, Korhonen: ἠγοράσομεν (“mixto imperfecto et aoristo ortum” Kaibel, see also IG 14.96)",{"loc":380,"note":439},{"_":440,"corr":441},"Franz: ἰίων; Kaibel, Wessel, Korhonen: ἰείων",[416,416],{"loc":382,"note":443},{"_":444,"corr":445,"unclear":448},"Franz: ν βάσιν; Kaibel suggested in apparatus ἐν πᾶκι? and Wessel ἐν ac (see also ἐν πάκης in IGCVO 602); Ferrua [ἠμι]ν ἔνβασιν; Korhonen [ἠμι]ν [?] ἔνβασιν (but also τὴ]ν is possible)",[446,447],"τῆ","e","p",{"type":450,"xml:lang":126,"resp":353,"p":451},"translation","((Chi-Rho)) Aurelios Rhestoutos and Zosime, we purchased this tomb at our expense.",{"type":450,"xml:lang":290,"resp":353,"p":453},"((Chi-Rho)) Aurelios Rhestoutos e Zosime, acquistammo questa tomba a nostre spese.",{"type":455,"resp":353,"p":456},"commentary",{"_":457,"ref":458,"foreign":474},"This is a marble plaque and not a sarcophagus, which must have served to mark a “loculus”, according to the interpretation that J. and L. Robert (BE 1964 nr. 631) gave for a similar inscription from Catania, RAC 8 (1931) 122-25 = . This inscription attests to the purchase of the tomb by the deceased who are buried in it: the names of the deceased are followed by the verb , an expression indicating that the purchase was made at their own expense () and by the object (for  as the tomb, see AE 1996.0792 =  and Ferrua 1958: 172). It is possible that there was a reflexive pronoun in the lacuna of l. 6, as in other cases where the deceased purchased the grave for himself: IMusCatania 229 = . For the registration of the purchase of the tomb in Christian epitaphs, see Führer and Schultze (1907: 12-15) and Korhonen (2004: 108-110). The cognomen of the deceased must have been Restitutus but for such a form, see ICUR 19782. The name of the woman, , is attested in other inscriptions of the city (CIL 10.7016 = , IMusCatania 165 = ) and more in general of Sicily (LGPN 3A: 190).",[459,462,465,468,471],{"_":460,"target":461},"ISic001547","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001547",{"_":463,"target":464},"ISic001423","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001423",{"_":466,"target":467},"ISic001628","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001628",{"_":469,"target":470},"ISic000300","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000300",{"_":472,"target":473},"ISic001649","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001649",[475,477,479,481],{"_":476,"xml:lang":110},"ἀγοράω",{"_":478,"xml:lang":110},"ἐκ τῶν ἰδίων",{"_":480,"xml:lang":110},"ἔνβασις",{"_":404,"xml:lang":110},{"type":483,"listBibl":484},"bibliography",[485,558],{"type":369,"bibl":486},[487,495,503,510,518,529,536,543,551],{"author":488,"date":489,"citedRange":490,"ptr":491,"ref":493},"Amico","1741","259 no.15",{"target":492},"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F5INCW3T",{"_":494,"target":494},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002186",{"author":496,"date":497,"citedRange":498,"ptr":499,"ref":501},"Torremuzza","1769","166 no.19",{"target":500},"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/SPTB56H3",{"_":502,"target":502},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084",{"author":496,"date":504,"citedRange":505,"ptr":506,"ref":508},"1784","173 no.19",{"target":507},"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/7PSFHSUH",{"_":509,"target":509},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083",{"author":511,"date":512,"citedRange":513,"ptr":514,"ref":516},"Ferrara","1829","349 no.1",{"target":515},"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/82T4IWDN",{"_":517,"target":517},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005"